snippet.textDisplay: Liquid has a lot of capacity to absorb heat, and can potentially transfer better than air as well, however in a liquid cooler there isn't much if any evaporation going on and evaporation actually results in more efficient transfer of heat. If you just spray water on something and then blow air past it to make the water evaporate, you can drop the surface temperature of that thing below ambient. That is why they spray water on the radiators of high performance drift cars, it improves the transfer of heat off of the fins and into the air as the water evaporates.
